    </ol>
  </nav>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero-fade">
    <div class="container-wide pt-16 pb-14">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
        <span class="eyebrow">Industry Playbook</span>
        <span class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-300">7 Jun 2026</span>
        <span class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-300">11 min read</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-5 max-w-3xl font-display text-4xl font-bold leading-tight grad-text md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
        AI Optimisation for Travel &amp; Hospitality
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-200">
        When travellers ask ChatGPT for a 10-day itinerary or Perplexity for the best boutique hotels in Lisbon,
        the brands that appear in those answers capture consideration at the highest-intent moment in the booking journey.
        <strong class="text-white">AI optimization for travel</strong> is the practice of ensuring your property,
        destination, or platform is cited accurately and consistently across every major generative engine.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Two-column layout -->
  <div class="container-wide py-12 lg:grid lg:grid-cols-[220px_1fr] lg:gap-12">

    <!-- Sticky TOC -->
    <aside class="hidden lg:block">
      <div class="sticky top-24">
        <span class="eyebrow">On this page</span>
        <nav class="toc mt-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5">
          {tocItems.map(item => (
            <a href={`#${item.id}`} data-toc-link>{item.label}</a>
          ))}
        </nav>
      </div>
    </aside>

    <!-- Main content -->
    <div>

      <!-- Key Takeaways -->
      <div class="card p-6 mb-12">
        <span class="eyebrow">Key Takeaways</span>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-200">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-[var(--accent)]">&#10003;</span>
            <span>Travel queries are among the most natural-language-heavy in AI search — itinerary, comparison, and "best for" queries dominate.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-[var(--accent)]">&#10003;</span>
            <span>Entity authority across booking directories (TripAdvisor, Booking.com, Google Maps) is the primary citation signal for travel properties.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-[var(--accent)]">&#10003;</span>
            <span>Review volume, recency, and structured review schema are material factors in whether AI cites a property over competitors.</span>
          </li>
