      </section>

      <!-- Section 6: Content Formats -->
      <section id="content-formats" class="anchor-top prose-dark mb-16">
        <h2>Content Formats That Get Cited in Travel AI Answers</h2>

        <p>
          <strong>Not all travel content is equally citable — the format of your content is as important as its topical relevance.</strong>
          These are the content patterns that consistently appear in AI-generated travel responses across platforms.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>Structured itinerary pages</strong> with explicit day headers (H2 or H3), named destinations, and specific time allocations
          are retrieved far more frequently than narrative travel articles for itinerary queries. Each day should open with a declarative
          summary sentence — "Day 3 focuses on the historical centre, within walking distance of the hotel" — rather than a discursive paragraph.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>Comparison tables</strong> covering properties, routes, or experiences within a defined category are the highest-value
          format for "best X" queries. Tables with columns for price tier, location, star rating, family-friendliness, and standout feature
          give AI systems structured data to extract and synthesise. Prose comparisons are less reliably extracted.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>FAQ-structured booking advice</strong> answers policy, logistics, and planning questions in the exact format AI systems
          prefer for extraction. "What is the check-in time at [property]?", "Is breakfast included in the standard rate?", and
          "How far is the property from the airport?" are all natural language queries where structured Q&amp;A content captures AI citations
          that generic page copy does not.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>Review aggregation with schema</strong> — publishing AggregateRating markup from verified platforms — gives AI retrieval
          systems a machine-readable signal about your property's standing relative to the destination category. A property with an
          AggregateRating of 9.2/10 from 1,400 reviews is a more confident citation than one with no structured rating data.
        </p>

        <p>
          For an overview of how these content principles connect to the broader discipline of AI brand visibility, see our
          <a href="/ai-brand-visibility/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">AI brand visibility guide</a>.
          To discuss a tailored strategy for your travel brand, visit our <a href="/geo-services/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">GEO services page</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

